# Planning in Todoist, not in code

## Where planning goes

- **Todoist (Auth project)** — tasks, subtasks, descriptions, acceptance criteria, next steps.
- **Repo docs** — contracts only: OpenAPI, validation matrix, data model, security contract (`docs/api/`, `docs/data-model.md`).
- **Chat** — alignment and decisions before implementation.

## Never put in code or user-facing UI

- Agent checklists, integration steps, module IDs for developers, or "replace this placeholder" instructions.
- Internal planning, follow-up notes, or discussion summaries.
- References to `AGENTS.md`, skills, or Todoist in screens users see.

Console placeholders for **unbuilt** nav items: minimal empty state only (e.g. "Not available yet"). No dev checklists.

## Todoist task shape

- **Parent module tasks** — high level (e.g. "M09: OAuth authorization server").
- **When starting work** — read the task, write a **detailed plan** in chat and/or as **subtasks** with concrete next steps.
- **More scope discovered** — add subtasks or follow-up tasks in Todoist; do not expand scope silently or document it in code.
- **Before closing a task** — every subtask done; plan in Todoist matches what shipped.

## Closing a task

A module task is **complete** only when all of its subtasks and acceptance criteria are verified — not when API tests pass alone. See `module-delivery.mdc`.
